Another key factor to consider when considering AS/400 vs PC/LAN
is that you can now get the both advantages of both with the AS/400.
The new Lan Server/400 product attaches an FSIOP card to the 400
to serve as a high-speed PC file server in addition to the AS/400's
enterprise serving. Since the FSIOP card has it's own processor,
you don't steal cycles from the main AS/400 processor which
is busy running your business applications.

The key thing is that you only have to administrate one machine -
NOT two.  You also get to leverage the advantages of all the AS/400 
administration and backup features on your PC server.  Currently,
the FSIOP supports OS/2 LAN Server with Novell Netware support
coming down the pipes.


